Wuffs — Wrangling Untrusted File Formats Safely
================================================

Upstream:    https://github.com/google/wuffs
Source:      release/c/wuffs-v0.3.c (string-to-double subset)
Commit:      988af1c03c6a23f3a90bd5f2c8529fd3cfa8daeb
License:     Apache-2.0 OR MIT (see LICENSE-Wuffs)

Files vendored
--------------
floatconv_wuffs.h    Single-header extract of Wuffs' float parser
                     (parse_number_f64 + HPD + Eisel-Lemire). ~2360 LOC.
LICENSE-Wuffs        Combined Apache-2.0 + MIT license text.

Used by which backends
----------------------
wuffs (parse)        — pure-C alternative to fast_float; pair with
                       format_backend=ryu_opt for fully zero-C++
                       operation on the float-formatting / parsing path.

Algorithm
---------
Eisel-Lemire fast path (~99.9999% of inputs) with High Precision
Decimal (HPD) fallback for the rest. No bigint, no dynamic allocation,
no platform strtod dependency. Correctly rounded for every input.

The bridge between Wuffs and CPython's `_Py_dg_strtod` calling
convention is src/cpython_adapter/{pystrtod_wuffs.h,wuffs_strtod.cc}.

Local modifications
-------------------
The header itself has substantial local modifications relative to
upstream Wuffs's full release headers — but they are vendoring-time
extractions, not algorithmic changes. From the file header:

  1. Removed all code outside string-to-double parsing.
  2. Added self-contained type definitions and utility inlines.
  3. Replaced WUFFS_BASE__MAYBE_STATIC with static.
  4. Replaced extern const char declarations with static definitions.
  5. Added _MSC_VER/_M_X64 branch to multiply_u64 and clz_u64.
  6. No algorithmic changes.

These edits are tracked by the dtoa_wuff branch on
https://github.com/eendebakpt/cpython and synced here verbatim.

Regeneration: tools/sync_wuffs.sh (default: copies from the
~/cpython0@dtoa_wuff vendored copy, which is the source of truth
until upstream Wuffs ships an equivalent single-header extract).
